spans.text: " A scrip with herbs and fruits supplied
its humble thatch Required a master's care
when busy crowds retire To take their evening rest
impart , To sooth the stranger's woe
those who prise the paltry thing " More trifling still than they
that lulls to sleep , " A shade that follows wealth or fame , " And leaves the wretch to weep
found " To warm the turtles nest
while he spoke , a rising blush His love-lorn guest betrayed
Swift mantling to the view , Like colours over the morning skies , As bright , as transient too
alarms , The lovely stranger stands confessed A maid in all her charms
The blossom opening to the day " The dews of heaven refined , "
